 <item> <title>Sixty Years after Brown: Where is the Outrage?</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/speeches/sixty-years-after-brown-where-outrage</link>
 <description>Secretary Duncan spoke both to why education is the civil rights issue of our generation and the unfulfilled promise of Brown v. Board of Education. Equity is a theme of virtually all the Obama administration&#039;s initiatives in education. The Secretary urged education reporters to aggressively report not only on achievement and opportunity gaps but on the &quot;courage gap&quot; and &quot;action gap.&quot;</description>
